

## ðŸ“Œ Projection

// Used to show only specific fields of a document

**Syntax:**
db.<collection>.find(query, { field: 1/0 })

**Example:**
db.students.find({}, { name: 1, age: 1, \_id: 0 })
// Shows only name and age fields, hides `_id`.

---

## ðŸ“Œ Embedded Documents

// A document stored inside another document (nested JSON)

**Syntax:**
db.<collection>.insertOne({ field1: value, embeddedField: { key1: value1, key2: value2 } })

**Example:**
db.students.insertOne({ name: "Shreyas", age: 22, address: { city: "Mumbai", pincode: 400001 } })
// `address` is an embedded document with city and pincode.

---

## ðŸ“Œ Update Operations

// Used to modify existing documents

**Syntax:**
db.<collection>.updateOne({ filter }, { \$set: { field: value } })

**Example 1 (update single):**
db.students.updateOne({ name: "Shreyas" }, { \$set: { age: 23 } })
// Updates Shreyasâ€™s age to 23.

**Example 2 (update many):**
db.students.updateMany({ age: 21 }, { \$set: { status: "Active" } })
// All students with age 21 get status = "Active".

---
